Operations Manager / IT Security Officer', 'All Branches', 'OPEN', 'Internal Audit System', '2026-04-25', 'Emmanuel Nkoulou', NULL, '2026-04-25 08:36:37'),
(67, 'HIGH', 'Transaction Monitoring', '[AUTO-C04] Orphaned Transaction References\n\n138 transaction(s) reference non-existent accounts.', 'WHAT: Some transactions in the system reference account numbers that do not exist in your accounts database. These are called &quot;orphaned references.&quot;\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: Transactions linked to non-existent accounts mean money may have moved to or from accounts that cannot be tracked. This creates audit trail gaps and could indicate data corruption, deleted accounts with active transactions, or fraud.\n\nHOW TO FIX: (1) Export the list of orphaned transactions from the check details. (2) For each transaction, determine if the account number was mistyped, if the account was closed/deleted, or if the transaction is fraudulent. (3) Re-link transactions to the correct accounts where possible. (4) Reverse any transactions that cannot be resolved. (5) Add a validation rule so future transactions can only reference active accounts.\n\nWHO: IT Systems Administrator / Head of Operations', 'KUMBA', 'CLOSED', 'Internal Audit System', '2026-04-25', 'Emmanuel Nkoulou', NULL, '2026-04-27 10:21:57'),
(68, 'HIGH', 'Risk Management', '[AUTO-C17] Loan-to-Deposit Ratio\n\nLDR is 0% (loans: 6 185 806 / deposits: 0 FCFA). Below optimal range.', 'WHAT: The Loan-to-Deposit Ratio (LDR) measures how much of the bank&#039;s customer deposits have been lent out. A healthy range is typically 30% to 90%.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: If the LDR is above 90%, the bank may not have enough liquidity to meet withdrawal demands. If below 30%, the bank is not using its deposit base efficiently to generate interest income.\n\nHOW TO FIX: (1) If LDR is above 90%: Reduce new lending, increase deposit mobilization campaigns, or consider securitizing some loans. (2) If LDR is below 30%: Review the lending strategy for growth opportunities, relax qualifying criteria where appropriate, or launch targeted loan products. (3) Set up automated alerts when the ratio approaches 80% or drops below 35%. (4) Review the LDR monthly as part of the Asset-Liability Committee (ALCO) process.\n\nWHO: Chief Risk Officer / Treasury Manager', 'KUMBA', 'CLOSED', 'Internal Audit System', '2026-04-25', 'Emmanuel Nkoulou', NULL, '2026-05-03 14:02:23'),
