(89, 'MEDIUM', 'Transaction Monitoring', '[AUTO-DS03] Off-Hours Transaction Activity\n\n109 transactions were posted outside normal business hours (before 6AM or after 6PM UTC). While some off-hours activity is expected — such as ATM withdrawals, mobile banking transfers, and automated batch processing — a high volume of off-hours transactions warrants review to ensure all activity is legitimate and properly authorized.\n\nMost recent off-hours transactions:\nTXN-20260425-0001 — 100 000 FCFA at 2026-04-24 23:02:04\nTXN-20260423-0032 — 100 000 FCFA at 2026-04-23 22:39:15\nTXN-20260423-0031 — 1 000 000 FCFA at 2026-04-23 21:55:54\nTXN-20260423-0030 — 2 000 000 FCFA at 2026-04-23 21:35:32\nTXN-20260423-0029 — 1 000 000 FCFA at 2026-04-23 21:34:13\nTXN-20260423-0028 — 1 000 000 FCFA at 2026-04-23 20:27:38\nTXN-20260422-0053 — 100 000 FCFA at 2026-04-22 22:48:23\nTXN-20260422-0052 — 3 767 FCFA at 2026-04-22 22:17:44\nTXN-20260422-0051 — 200 000 FCFA at 2026-04-22 22:17:43\nTXN-20260422-0050 — 200 000 FCFA at 2026-04-22 22:17:41', 'WHAT: A significant number of transactions were posted outside normal business hours.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: Off-hours transactions can be a sign of unauthorized access, after-hours manipulation of accounts, or automated processing errors. While many off-hours transactions are legitimate (ATMs, mobile banking, batch jobs), the volume detected exceeds typical patterns and should be reviewed.\n\nHOW TO FIX: (1) Review each off-hours transaction to determine the channel (ATM, mobile, branch, batch). (2) For branch-initiated transactions outside business hours, verify the authorization and identify the staff member who posted them. (3) If batch processing explains the volume, document the batch schedule and verify all batch jobs are authorized. (4) Implement channel-specific monitoring so ATM and mobile transactions are separated from staff-initiated ones. (5) Set up alerts for staff-initiated transactions posted outside business hours.\n\nWHO: Branch Operations Manager / IT Security Officer', 'All Branches', 'OPEN', 'Internal Audit System', '2026-04-25', 'Emmanuel Nkoulou', NULL, '2026-04-25 16:33:13'),
