(139, 'MEDIUM', 'Risk Management', '[AUTO-DS01] Active Accounts with Zero Balance\n\n5 customer accounts are currently marked as ACTIVE but have a ledger balance of zero. While some of these may be newly opened accounts that have not yet received funds, a large number of zero-balance active accounts can indicate dormant accounts that were never properly reclassified, or accounts created for purposes other than legitimate banking.\n\nAffected accounts (first 10): ACC-200100013, ACC-200100012, ACC-200100008, ACC-200100010, ACC-200100006', 'WHAT: A significant number of active accounts have zero balance. These accounts may be dormant, unused, or potentially created for illegitimate purposes.\n\nWHY IT MATTERS: Zero-balance active accounts that are not properly classified can be exploited for money laundering or used to circumvent transaction monitoring. They also inflate active account counts, giving a false picture of the bank&#039;s customer base.\n\nHOW TO FIX: (1) Review each zero-balance account to determine when it was opened and whether any transaction has ever occurred. (2) Contact account holders to confirm their intention to use the account. (3) Reclassify accounts with no activity for 90+ days as DORMANT per bank policy. (4) Close accounts that customers confirm are no longer needed. (5) Implement automated dormancy detection that flags accounts with zero balance and no transactions for 60+ days.\n\nWHO: Branch Operations Manager / Compliance Officer', 'All Branches', 'OPEN', 'Internal Audit System', '2026-04-27', 'Emmanuel Nkoulou', NULL, '2026-04-27 10:21:51'),
